    "recap_headline": "Brown University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "SOUTH ORANGE, N.J. \u2013\nA pair of unearned runs undid the Brown baseball team in a 3-1 loss on Sunday afternoon in the rubber match of a three-game series at Seton Hall.\nSenior\nDylan Reid\nstarted on the mound for Brown and allowed just one earned run on three hits with three strikeouts over 5.0 innings.\nBrenden Kline\ndid not allow an earned run over 2.0 innings of work, and\nChristian Keel\ntossed a scoreless inning. Offensively,\nMark Henshon\nhad a hit, walk and run scored.\nSeton Hall outhit Brown 7-4 in the game and got on the board in the second inning when a baserunner raced home from third on a throw down to second on a steal attempt.\nThe pitcher's duel continued into the sixth inning when SHU scored another run on a two-out error, followed by a single. Another unearned run in the seventh made it a SHU 3-0 lead.\nThe Bears got one run back in the eighth inning, putting four straight runners aboard after two outs. After two hits and a hit batter loaded the bases,\nLogan Meusy\nwas hit by a pitch to force in a run.\nThe Bears will return home on Wednesday afternoon to host Northeastern at Attanasio Family Field at Murray Stadium. First pitch is set for 3 p.m. on ESPN+.\nBROWN UNIVERSITY SPORTS FOUNDATION\nThe Brown University Sports Foundation (BUSF) is the backbone of our athletics program, playing a crucial role in enhancing the student-athlete experience.\u00a0This\u00a0is possible through philanthropic support from our alumni, parents, fans, and friends.\u00a0Your\u00a0gift through the Sports Foundation can immediately impact today's Brown Bears, helping them excel in the classroom, in competition, and, most importantly, in the community. Please click\nhere\nto learn more about how\u00a0you\u00a0can support the Bears.\nFOLLOW US ON SOCIAL\nFor the latest on Brown Athletics, please follow\n@BrownU_Bears\non X and\n@BrownU_Bears\non Instagram. Like\nBrownUBears\non Facebook and subscribe to the\nBrownAthletics\nYouTube channel."
